# 📘 AWS Full Network Flow (End-to-End Debug Guide)

---

# 🧠 🔥 Complete Request Flow (Internet → Application)

```text id="f1d8j3"
User → DNS (Route53) → Load Balancer → Route Table → Subnet → NACL → Security Group → EC2/Pod → Application
```

---

# 🚀 Step-by-Step Flow

---

## 1️⃣ DNS Resolution

* User hits:

```text id="s9tq2g"
www.myapp.com
```

* Resolved by:
  👉 Amazon Route 53

* Returns:

```text id="9lgz3m"
Load Balancer DNS/IP
```

---

## 2️⃣ Load Balancer

* Receives request
* Handles:

  * Routing
  * TLS termination (if HTTPS)

---

## 🔐 TLS / SSL Layer

```text id="v6j5dn"
Client → HTTPS → Load Balancer (TLS termination)
```

* Certificate attached to LB
* Decrypts request

---

## 3️⃣ Route Table (Path Decision)

👉 Role:

> Decides WHERE traffic goes

Example:

```text id="o1a6x7"
0.0.0.0/0 → IGW
10.0.0.0/16 → local
```

---

## 4️⃣ Subnet

👉 Logical network segment

Types:

---

### 🟢 Public Subnet

```text id="q6i8kl"
0.0.0.0/0 → IGW
```

* Internet → EC2 ✅
* EC2 → Internet ✅

---

### 🔵 Private Subnet

```text id="h4k3p9"
0.0.0.0/0 → NAT Gateway
```

* Internet → EC2 ❌
* EC2 → Internet ✅

---

### ⚫ Isolated Subnet

```text id="t2x9lm"
No 0.0.0.0/0 route
```

* No internet access

---

## 5️⃣ NACL (Subnet Firewall)

👉 Role:

> Controls traffic at subnet level

### Features:

* Stateless
* Requires inbound + outbound rules

---

### Example:

```text id="y3p7qa"
Inbound:  ALLOW 80
Outbound: DENY ALL ❌
```

👉 Result:

* Request reaches EC2
* Response blocked

---

## 6️⃣ Security Group (Instance Firewall)

👉 Role:

> Controls traffic at instance level

### Features:

* Stateful
* Only inbound rules needed

---

### Example:

```text id="m8w2zr"
Inbound: ALLOW 80
```

👉 Response automatically allowed

---

## 7️⃣ EC2 / Pod (Application Layer)

* Application processes request
* May call:

  * DB
  * Cache
  * External APIs

---

# 🔁 Response Flow

```text id="n4q7yt"
Application → SG → NACL → Route Table → IGW → User
```

---

# 🌐 Outbound Flow (EC2 → Internet)

---

## 🟢 Public Subnet

```text id="x7k9vf"
EC2 → Route Table → IGW → Internet
```

---

## 🔵 Private Subnet

```text id="p3m6ra"
EC2 → Route Table → NAT → IGW → Internet
```

---

# ⚖️ Core Components Summary

---

## 🛣️ Route Table

* Decides path
* Does NOT block

---

## 🚧 NACL

* Subnet firewall
* Stateless
* Blocks/Allows traffic

---

## 🚪 Security Group

* Instance firewall
* Stateful
* Final access control

---

# 🧠 Debug Flow (VERY IMPORTANT)

```text id="z8q1ws"
1. DNS (Route53)
2. Load Balancer
3. Target Group
4. Route Table
5. NACL
6. Security Group
7. EC2 / Pod
8. Application
```

---

# 🚨 Common Failure Mapping

| Issue                           | Likely Cause            |
| ------------------------------- | ----------------------- |
| Cannot reach app                | Route table / IGW issue |
| Request reaches but no response | NACL outbound blocked   |
| Connection refused              | Security Group          |
| 503 error                       | No healthy targets      |
| 502 error                       | Backend issue           |
| HTTPS not working               | SSL/TLS misconfig       |
| Timeout                         | SG / NACL / network     |

---

# 🎯 Key Interview One-Liners

* “Route table defines path, not permission”
* “NACL is stateless, requires inbound and outbound rules”
* “Security group is stateful, return traffic is automatic”
* “Public subnet has route to IGW”
* “Private subnet uses NAT Gateway”
* “TLS is usually terminated at Load Balancer”

---

